us.phonetic: /adv. ˈoʊvɚˈhɛd; adj., n. ˈoʊvɚˌhɛd/, (adv. ō′vər hed′; adj., n. ō′vər hed′)

example.eg: The crowd looked up at the planes circling overhead.
example.egtrans: 人群看着头顶盘旋的飞机。

example.eg: Those overhead cables supply the town's electricity.
example.egtrans: 这些高架电缆向城市供应电力。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 头顶的, 顶上的, 高架

example.eg: John puts his case in the overhead.
example.egtrans: 约翰将自己的箱子放在头顶行李舱中。

example.eg: This business has very high overheads.
example.egtrans: 这家公司的日常开支很高。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 一般管理费用，日常开支

us.phonetic: /adv. ˈoʊvɚˈhɛd; adj., n. ˈoʊvɚˌhɛd/, (adv. ō′vər hed′; adj., n. ō′vər hed′)

example.eg: Natalie used an overhead for her presentation.
Angela won the point by hitting an overhead.

us.phonetic: /adv. ˈoʊvɚˈhɛd; adj., n. ˈoʊvɚˌhɛd/, (adv. ō′vər hed′; adj., n. ō′vər hed′)

trans_examp.trans_cn: 让...无法理解, 是...理解不了的

us.phonetic: /adv. ˈoʊvɚˈhɛd; adj., n. ˈoʊvɚˌhɛd/, (adv. ō′vər hed′; adj., n. ō′vər hed′)

example.eg: For today's meeting I'll need the OHP.
Please be careful when you open the overhead lockers, as items may have shifted in flight.

trans_examp.trans_cn: 行李架, 上部置物架

example.eg: David places the transparency on the overhead projector so that everyone in the room can see it.
The image from the transparency is projected onto the overhead projector screen.
